PyTorch's c10/macros/Macros.h forward-declares __assert_fail "matching glibc exactly"
(noexcept, unsigned int line) for CUDA/SYCL/ROCm device asserts. musl declares it
differently (_Noreturn, int line), so on musl the redeclaration conflicts:
  error: exception specification in declaration does not match previous declaration
We build LibTorch CPU-only, so this device-assert forward declaration is unnecessary;
gate the whole block to glibc. clang on musl does not define __GLIBC__.

Applies to PyTorch 2.5.x. Apply from the pytorch source root with: git apply -p1
--
diff --git a/c10/macros/Macros.h b/c10/macros/Macros.h
index ab6f2b3..6897a10 100644
--- a/c10/macros/Macros.h
+++ b/c10/macros/Macros.h
@@ -392,7 +392,7 @@ __host__ __device__
            0);                                   \
   }
 #else // __APPLE__, _MSC_VER
-#if defined(NDEBUG)
+#if defined(NDEBUG) && defined(__GLIBC__)
 extern "C" {
 #if defined(__SYCL_DEVICE_ONLY__)
 extern SYCL_EXTERNAL void __assert_fail(
